Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.07,0:00:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get the list of attendees?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.64,0:00:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.78,0:00:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a very good idea\Nof who was there then and their location.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.25,0:00:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The shooter was targeting\Nthe governor, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.28,0:00:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All the guests were VIPs,\Nso they all probably have enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.42,0:00:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue examining the connection\Nbetween them and the shooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.33,0:00:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like the Frankfurt Police are\Nin a tizzy over the convention shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.86,0:00:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Even though they know\Nthe shooter's identity,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.03,0:00:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't know who he was targeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So they know who the shooter was.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.57,0:00:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He was a dentist\Nfrom the redevelopment district.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.58,0:00:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A dentist, huh? Dang.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.41,0:00:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.95,0:00:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I was planning on visiting the dentist\Nas soon as I retired.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been so busy every day\Nthat I haven't been able to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.89,0:00:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But I sure don't want\Nsome dentist with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector, over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.63,0:01:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.97,0:01:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Inspector Weissbach\Nof the North Rhine-Westphalia Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.09,0:02:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinhard Dinger, age 42. Taxi driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.83,0:02:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspected in the murder\Nof a passenger in Gunter Forest Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Also suspected in the 1997 murder\Nof a Bilker Investment Bank employee,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.77,0:02:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1996 Hofgarten murder,\Nand the 1995 Rhine Riverside murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.58,0:03:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Since all these murders occurred\Nin and around Düsseldorf,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.25,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the suspect is wanted there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.32,0:03:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That being said, I requested
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.02,0:03:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the said suspect's transfer\Nto North Rhine-Westphalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.83,0:03:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, is everything ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.70,0:03:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.93,0:03:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.21,0:03:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.65,0:03:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.42,0:03:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.49,0:03:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.09,0:03:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Smoking is not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.52,0:03:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a no-smoking car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.29,0:03:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.03,0:03:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you'd always stuck\Nto your strong morals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how many people have you killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you counting\Nthe precious lives you took?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.58,0:04:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember your victims?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my last assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I retire tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a flashy career\Nas a detective, but it wasn't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.17,0:04:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can putter around in my garden\Nwith my wife and live life leisurely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.48,0:04:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what life's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you regret\Nstealing those simple pleasures of life
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when they're someone\Nwho would spit on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The rider I picked up on Addler Street\Nspat at me when he got out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.50,0:04:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me\Nthat's the reason you killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.17,0:05:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who would spit on a person\Nis scum. Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The couple I gave a ride to\Nat Gerresheim Station was even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.11,0:05:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They started coupling\Nin the back seat of my cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.42,0:05:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The back seat of my very own car!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.79,0:05:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I killed the two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.79,0:05:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A young alcoholic punk\Nwith a non-stop filthy mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.20,0:05:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A hooker who tried to pay\Nthe fare with her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.47,0:05:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,An old hag who stank of perfume\Nand insulted everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had all kinds of shitty riders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.37,0:05:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.64,0:05:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.92,0:05:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.49,0:05:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the murder\Nof the Bilker Investment Bank employee?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.19,0:05:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How was he scum?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.83,0:06:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a hard worker and an honest person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.36,0:06:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved his family as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But because you killed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.34,0:06:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the corporate corruption scandal\Nhe was going to blow the whistle on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,remains shrouded in mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.58,0:06:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That one…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-It left a bad taste in my mouth.\N-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.75,0:06:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to you.\NAll your talk of righteous punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.49,0:06:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was nothing but a way\Nto justify your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That one… I didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean someone made you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.58,0:06:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, there's no smoking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.59,0:07:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you ever\Ntry to smoke around me again,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.82,0:07:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.89,0:07:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck turned you\Ninto this kind of person?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always been a person\Nwith strict morals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.27,0:07:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got a little push, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, a man was\Nwalking his dog in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.05,0:07:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All the dog did was poop,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.75,0:07:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but the man started\Nkicking the dog for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The poor dog was trembling and scared,\Nbut all it had done was take a poop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.11,0:07:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When I came to my senses,\Nthe police were restraining me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.12,0:08:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I saw a young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.25,0:08:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy told the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.33,0:08:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's not his fault.\NThe man with the dog hit him first."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the police decided not to arrest me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.64,0:08:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I told the boy thanks\Nand offered to drive him home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.87,0:08:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he didn't have a home to go to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.58,0:08:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, he brought his sister\Nout from the bushes in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.12,0:08:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,His twin sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.35,0:08:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured all I could do was\Nbring them both to my apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even weirder,\Nwhen they took off their jackets,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they were both wearing pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.06,0:08:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like\Nthey'd run away from a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.03,0:08:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,\Nthe boy had a bandage around his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.10,0:08:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, after eating dinner,\NI watched the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.97,0:09:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Like always,\NI muttered to myself, cursing the news,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.11,0:09:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this stupid world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and stupid people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.98,0:09:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"Scum should die!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think the boy told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.63,0:09:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "You're right."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.33,0:09:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he told me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need people like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.31,0:09:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard that, I felt liberated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.51,0:09:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.58,0:09:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying\Nthat's when you started killing people?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're through, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.33,0:09:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:09:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Your final assignment is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.83,0:10:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. All that's left for me\Nis to clean out my desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.00,0:10:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for all your years\Nof service, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel a little discouraged though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.41,0:10:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have a few unsolved cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.39,0:10:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He brought out his sister.\NHis twin sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.90,0:10:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They were both wearing pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.10,0:10:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like\Nthey'd run away from a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.67,0:10:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you remember that night for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.41,0:10:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything at all.\NAnything that you can remember at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Anna. Anna Liebert.\NIsn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.12,0:10:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,\Nthe boy had a bandage around his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.56,0:11:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those twins, they're nowhere to be found!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.70,0:11:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.60,0:11:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.97,0:11:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When did I come across those kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.04,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see…\NI think it was about 11 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.98,0:11:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What were they like?\NWhat did the kids look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.95,0:11:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Those they were blonde\Nwith very pretty faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.39,0:11:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That was those twins who disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.27,0:11:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The twins hold the key\Nto Dr. Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.05,0:11:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 30 hours until I retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.45,0:12:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A vampire, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.09,0:12:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You also murdered 13 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.03,0:12:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,ISENBURG DETENTION CENTER\N(FRANKFURT)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You say you can't live\Nunless you drink blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.36,0:12:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs to be virgin blood too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.67,0:12:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.17,0:12:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.44,0:12:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months ago, you murdered the girl\Nof a family that owns a general store,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.01,0:12:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Frieder Schelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you drink her blood too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.91,0:12:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As you've said,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.15,0:12:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone you've killed\Nso far has been a virgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.32,0:12:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You only killed them\Nafter a thorough investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.06,0:12:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is quite clear just how important\Nvirgin blood is to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.86,0:12:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This Frieder Schelling,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,though she still looked like a teenager,\Nwas 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.61,0:12:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But that isn't the issue here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.61,0:13:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She had worked at a cafe on Zeiler Street\Nin Frankfurt since she was 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.51,0:13:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very close to a famous high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.52,0:13:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She was like a goddess\Nto the boys who attended that school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.82,0:13:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,she had a child when she was 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.76,0:13:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumors say the father was a student\Nat the high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After giving birth,\Nher parents opened a general store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The story is\Nthat the student's parents were wealthy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.37,0:13:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the family opened the store\Nwith the bundle of money they were paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.41,0:13:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.42,0:13:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you investigated her\Njust as much as you did the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.62,0:13:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you also drink the blood\Nof non-virgin girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That one left a bad taste in my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.53,0:13:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I met the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:13:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.17,0:14:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When I met him,\NI realized that someone like me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was nothing but a bat\Nonly aspiring to become a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.55,0:14:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He is truly the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he ask you to kill her?\NWho was he? Where did you meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.36,0:14:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Griesheim in the Frankfurt suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.26,0:14:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a park there\Nlike those you can find anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.20,0:14:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the sandbox in that park,\Nhe wrote her name with a stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.31,0:14:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.25,0:14:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wrote it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.41,0:14:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I told you, the real vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.75,0:14:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,PINNEBERG PRISON\N(HAMBURG)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.55,0:14:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it,\Nit makes no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.26,0:14:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your murder\Nof Erich Klemperer was four months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.76,0:14:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, you'd only been ordered\Nto kill in Lower Saxony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.36,0:15:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So why did you go all the way\Nto Frankfurt just for this murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the aliens\Nalso send you a message to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.77,0:15:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the aliens suddenly change their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.18,0:15:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and send you a message\Nto go to Frankfurt and kill someone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.61,0:15:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was there some other reason you did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.38,0:15:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This Mr. Klemperer did have\Na sordid history.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.72,0:15:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,INVESTIGATIVE REPORT\NMISSING PERSON: ERICH KLEMPERER
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.62,0:15:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Cold War,\Nhe defected from East Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.46,0:15:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,These last few years,\Nhis food trading company was doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are rumors that he assisted
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.97,0:15:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the smuggling of children\Nfrom the East to the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.20,0:15:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.51,0:15:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he sold children from the East\Nto wealthy childless couples in the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.31,0:15:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a message.\NI met face-to-face with one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was overwhelmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.29,0:15:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A real alien stood right before my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.36,0:15:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did its UFO land?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At a park in Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.83,0:16:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His language\Nis the language of the aliens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to make it easy for me to understand,\Nhe wrote the name in the sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.48,0:16:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you could have felt\Nthe amazement that I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.48,0:16:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,DÜSSELDORF STATE POLICE
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.22,0:16:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to see you go,\NInspector Weissbach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.86,0:16:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.29,0:16:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a matter of hours\Nbefore you retire now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you're just happy to get rid of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we're celebrating\Ngetting rid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're having a big party later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.67,0:16:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like it will be an unpleasant one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.08,0:16:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Dr. Gillen.\NHe's a criminal psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.35,0:17:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's come to interview\Nthat serial murderer taxi driver, Dinger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.23,0:17:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone ask him to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.86,0:17:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He said it's\Nfor some research he's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.73,0:17:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's influential in his field,\Nso he's got pull with the top brass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when your rider\Ngot out and spit on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.64,0:17:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you ran him with your car and killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.22,0:17:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I've said many times\Nin interrogation, every person I killed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.59,0:17:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,were people we don't need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,People like you\Ndon't understand my righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.13,0:17:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Righteousness, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So can I ask you another question?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, you're very talkative\Nduring interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but when it comes to your murder\Nof Mr. Overt of Bilker Investment Bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.41,0:17:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you seem to clam up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.24,0:17:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,For all your other murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.84,0:18:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the records show how you proclaimed\Nthe righteousness of your deeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.38,0:18:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But with the murder of Mr. Overt,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.85,0:18:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you have yet to give\Na clear reason why you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.96,0:18:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm through talking with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.10,0:18:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go, Dr. Gillen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.50,0:18:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Inspector Weissbach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.50,0:18:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Dinger say anything\Nthat piqued your academic interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.64,0:18:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He only said\Nwhat was already in his record.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.75,0:18:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something\NI'd like to ask him as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.13,0:18:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be retiring today, so I feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.10,0:18:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to rest right\Nuntil I find this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.43,0:18:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How does this seem to you academically?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.64,0:18:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.37,0:19:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose there was a child\Nwho's like a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.97,0:19:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When he grows up, he goes to the man\Nwho helped him when he was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.65,0:19:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A child who's like a monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.05,0:19:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it sounds absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.72,0:19:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me more about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you two want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.50,0:19:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I said\NI wasn't talking to that academic again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still a detective,\Nuntil the end of today at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.90,0:19:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is an interrogation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.24,0:19:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, you told me about those twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.24,0:19:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that the boy liberated you,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.41,0:19:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If that boy grew up and came to you\Nand asked you to do something,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.25,0:19:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,would you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.07,0:20:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.84,0:20:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you kill Fritz Overt\Nfrom Bilker Investment Bank
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.04,0:20:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at the request of someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.75,0:20:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A hard worker and an honest person.\NThat's the kind of man Mr. Overt was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.82,0:20:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't in any way\Nlike the people you call scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.66,0:20:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about to blow the whistle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.93,0:20:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on a certain conglomerate's corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.19,0:20:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think he was scum,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.60,0:20:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that shatters the righteousness\Nyou claim for all your murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.61,0:20:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't asked to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.01,0:20:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He and I don't need words to communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.78,0:20:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.58,0:20:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To him, that bank employee\Nmust have been scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.82,0:20:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.99,0:20:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.73,0:21:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this man one of the twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.80,0:21:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When and where did you meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.60,0:21:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At a park in the Griesheim neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.47,0:21:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Griesheim in the Frankfurt suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At a park in Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.11,0:21:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote a name in the sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.08,0:21:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't say a word,\Nbut I knew what he meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.26,0:21:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted me to kill\Nthe man with this name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.86,0:21:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need words to communicate.\NWe understand each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.33,0:21:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We know\Nthat we don't need people like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.27,0:21:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.24,0:21:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that same person
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.27,0:21:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,asked the three men you interviewed\Nto commit murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.28,0:21:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,By using three unrelated serial murderers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.02,0:21:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he hid the purpose behind\Nthe three murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.05,0:22:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the three murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.76,0:22:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?\NTell me what you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.83,0:22:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma and Nina are\Nboth headed to Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.50,0:22:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.57,0:22:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying to…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.88,0:22:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,start something in Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.67,0:23:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitle translation by: Brian Athey
